							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/barriekreinik/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Barrie-Kreinik-1-scaled-e1716535199440-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Barrie Kreinik" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/barriekreinik/">Barrie Kreinik</a></h6>
										Barrie Kreinik is an actor, singer, writer, and award-winning audiobook narrator based in New York City. She is the author of the original audio drama <em>The Queen of Fourteenth Street</em> (Hachette Audio/June 4) and has published essays for <em>Months to Years</em> and <em>Theaterhound</em>. She also writes a creative nonfiction blog called <em>Points of View</em>.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
